article.headline: Monmouth (N.J.) 83, Wagner 61
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Tyler Azzarelli and Blake Hamilton each scored 18 points and Monmouth dealt Wagner its ninth straight loss, 83-61 Wednesday night. Marques Alston added 15 points for the Hawks (3-8, 2-0 Northeast Conference), who led 38-34 advantage at the break. Matt Vitale and Sean Munson each scored 14 points for the Seahawks (1-11, 0-3). Munson added 12 rebounds, finishing with his fifth double-double of the season, and the 13th of his career. Monmouth finished with 26 assists, including seven by Azzarelli. Alston scored seven points in a 16-4 run at the start of the second, helping the Hawks to a 54-38.
